From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Artjom W. <aco.art@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 1 Apr 2026 14:47:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] sunxi: mmc: keep probing mmc0 with broken card detect

On affected Vontar H618 TV boxes the mmc0 card-detect GPIO is unreliable
in U-Boot proper. When CONFIG_MMC_BROKEN_CD is enabled, keep probing
slot 0 instead of failing early with "no card present".

Assisted-by: Artjom W. <aco.art@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/mmc/sunxi_mmc.c | 7 +++++++
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/mmc/sunxi_mmc.c b/drivers/mmc/sunxi_mmc.c
--- a/drivers/mmc/sunxi_mmc.c
+++ b/drivers/mmc/sunxi_mmc.c
@@ -597,6 +597,13 @@ static int sunxi_mmc_getcd(struct udevice *dev)
 	if ((mmc->cfg->host_caps & MMC_CAP_NONREMOVABLE) ||
 	    (mmc->cfg->host_caps & MMC_CAP_NEEDS_POLL))
 		return 1;
+
+	/*
+	 * On affected Vontar H618 TV boxes CD GPIO can be unreliable in U-Boot
+	 * proper. Keep probing mmc0 instead of failing with "no card present".
+	 */
+	if (IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_MMC_BROKEN_CD) && priv->mmc_no == 0)
+		return 1;
 
 	if (dm_gpio_is_valid(&priv->cd_gpio)) {
 		int cd_state = dm_gpio_get_value(&priv->cd_gpio);
-- 
